<emphasis bold="true" box="[1439,1574,2026,2060]" pageId="96" pageNumber="696">Breeding.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1438,2577,2066,2100]" pageId="96" pageNumber="696" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="96.[1438,2646,1475,2258]" box="[1438,2577,2066,2100]" pageId="96" pageNumber="696">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1438,1673,2066,2100]" pageId="96" pageNumber="696">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Dollman’s Mosaic-tailed Rat is a terrestrial and arboreal species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1439,2378,2105,2139]" pageId="96" pageNumber="696" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="96.[1438,2646,1475,2258]" box="[1439,2378,2105,2139]" pageId="96" pageNumber="696">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1439,2139,2105,2139]" pageId="96" pageNumber="696">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="96" pageNumber="696" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="96.[1438,2646,1475,2258]" pageId="96" pageNumber="696">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1439,1787,2146,2180]" pageId="96" pageNumber="696">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List owing toits extensive range, lack of threats, and tolerance of disturbance.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
